    <item>
      <title>SS: Untitled</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/ss-untitled/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/ss-untitled/</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 28 Mar 2024 23:17:43 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;SS: Untitled&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;T/N: Duchess kept begging me to translate it, so you can thank her for the existence of this translation lol&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;This is a writing exercise written back in 2014 (i.e. just before the rewrite of arc 2/3), so it &lt;em&gt;probably &lt;/em&gt;isn&amp;#8217;t canon.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-center"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project 1: Maomao&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The subject is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;Character: Maomao&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Genre: Romance&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Tag: Yandere&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The day Jinshi visited Maomao’s apothecary, he was &lt;em&gt;exhausted&lt;/em&gt;. He usually came over on his days off, once every ten days, but every time he would have heavy bags under his eyes, looking like he was about to nod off. It was much worse today.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Jinshi-sama, will you rest today?”　&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao’s apothecary was a single room she rented from Rokushoukan. The brothel didn’t get customers during the day. The prostitutes would either be taking naps or grinding tea, so there were a lot of rooms available.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;No courtesans,” he said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I understand.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There was once a time when Jinshi looked outright fatigued so Maomao rented him the highest floor at Rokushoukan. In her belief that a gentleman’s fatigue had to be a result of being pent up, she had arranged for bathhouse prostitutes in the bathroom, as well as a whole range of courtesans, virgins included. And yet, when he arrived, let alone crook his fingers, he got angry. He got so angry it made Maomao wonder if he was actually bent instead, regretting that she hadn’t arranged for male prostitutes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Turns out his fatigue wasn’t fatigue in &lt;em&gt;that sense&lt;/em&gt;. Men were truly complex creatures.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao guided Jinshi up the stairs. He was so unsteady on his feet that it looked like he would topple over, so she wondered if she should have a manservant carry him up, but he adamantly refused. She had picked someone with a decent face to not hurt the courtesans’ feelings, but it seemed he didn’t swing that way. It was a good thing she hadn’t called for the male prostitutes.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Gaoshun, Jinshi’s aide, followed them with a look of concern.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The madam had laid out soft bedding on the top floor of Rokushoukan. The old bag who usually sat cross-legged, smoking from her pipe, was once a highly sought-after courtesan. If she really had to, Maomao could do the odd jobs the apprentice girls did, sing, dance and even play Go. The woman who gave birth to Maomao was also trained by this old lady, and she was also the one who had taken over the training of the Rokushoukan’s Three Princesses who had been that woman’s apprentices.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When the source of revenue, uh, Jinshi arrived, the madam bowed her head and leisurely withdrew. An incense for restful sleep was lit in the corner of the room.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(Huh?)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao took a whiff of the incense. Its components were a little different from the usual.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(It shouldn’t harm the body.)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She was a little uneasy about what the madam did, but the crone was an amazingly nice person to financial supporters. All the more so if the financial supporter possessed political power.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;So long as Jinshi didn’t lose his standing, the madam would have this man as the maximum priority. Although, if someone with more money and power were to come, she would switch over to them.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi changed into sleepwear and laid down on the futon. The madam made herself scarce and the worrywart attendant waited in the room next door.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao opened the window. A breeze rushed in, warming up the interior of the room. The fragrance of the incense had been a little too strong.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She rested her hand on the bannisters and looked outside.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Rokushoukan was the tallest building in the pleasure district. The top floor, which was this room, could look out over not just the pleasure district but the entire capital.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The pleasure district with its striking roofs, the rows of private houses in stained hues, and the castle town in refined shades of colour. And beyond that, the magnificent residence of the people of the heavens.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Perhaps it was because it was spring, it was hazy. With the sand particles in the air carried over from far, far away, the beautiful imperial palace looked ever more distant.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was a marvel that she had been at that place. It was also a marvel to believe that the person who was fast asleep, depending on the situation, had the potential to be the ruler of that castle.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi was the imperial brother. Currently, the emperor had a son–a young imperial prince who was appointed as the crown prince–but a child growing to adulthood wasn’t a surety. If not that, if anything were to befall the emperor, even if Jinshi doesn’t assume the throne, he would have to work as the regent.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(He’s quite secure.)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The young man sleeping on the futon was an important person in this country–Maomao couldn’t help wondering if she had been too relaxed about that fact.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;His coming to the pleasure district every time he had a break would give rise to bad rumours.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Of course, Jinshi had come over in secret by bringing with him the minimum number of guards and changing his clothes.&amp;nbsp; If he were to show up with his bare face, it would be clear as day who he was, as he possessed a charm that could fell birds from the sky with a mere gaze, a charm of which was finally reduced by half with a knife scar that marred his face.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;If he were a woman, he could cause the downfall of a nation, and that wouldn’t be out of the question even as a man. He was that much of a beauty.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao had lived in places that gathered beauties–the inner palace and the pleasure district. She still had yet to meet anyone more beautiful than him.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(Truly a face that’s too much.)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Had he been a younger sister, the emperor would have had many uses for him, like diplomacy for instance. It was unfortunate he was born a man, a tough reality. No, to not summon turmoil in these peaceful times, he was better off as a man.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao was about to leave the room while thinking of such rude things.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She heard Jinshi grumble in his sleep. She considered ignoring him but then got closer and sat down. If he didn’t get a good sleep, it would be bad, she thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi’s brows were furrowed. He groaned.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(Could he be having a nightmare?)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Noticing that his lips looked dry, Maomao wet a cotton ball with fruit juice and had Jinshi suck on it. The image of his shapely lips sucking on the cotton looked somewhat naughty. If anyone other than Maomao from Rokushoukan were doing this to him, something in their minds would shatter and they would mount Jinshi.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(This man is truly sinful just by being alive.)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;His charm was strong to the point that it flustered his long-serving aide Gaoshun at times. Some beasts have a scent that would attract the opposite sex&amp;#8211;this man didn’t have just his appearance, but must also have copious amounts of that scent, she thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(It would probably sell well as a perfume after I could distil that and put it up for sale.)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She found herself thinking of something ridiculous. For the time being, she wondered if she should auction the nightwear he wore to people with eccentric tastes later, but the madam had already done such a thing, so that’d be out of the question, huh.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Everyone around Maomao would tell her that she was strange to think like this. The Three Princesses of Rokushoukan in particular would tell her so time and time again.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao lacked the emotions of a woman.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Despite being told such a thing, it was inevitable. Since birth, the only thing she saw was men and women selling such and such. She never had a maternal figure either. If it wasn’t for her dad raising her, she might have turned out worse as a person. Her adoptive father, Luomen, had firmly taught Maomao what it meant to be a human. What would happen if he only taught her medicine?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;So Maomao thought as she looked at the sleeping figure before her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She could see severed fingers from the hand that stuck out from the bedding. It had grown a bit, but it didn’t return to normal.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(Did my medicine actually work?)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She had no way of comparing, but in reality, she had no confidence in whether it worked. It was something you’d be able to tell if you cut down the fingers of the right hand in the same way as the left side.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There probably wasn’t anyone who would do that for her. Thus, Maomao used herself to test out the medicine.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;What would happen if someone telling her that she could use their body to her heart&amp;#8217;s content appeared before her? And also supposing that, at the time, her dad who created the meaning of her humanity wasn’t around.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Surely, she would go down an inhumane path. Her curiosity was that strong. Once it got to that point, she would no longer be able to walk openly under the sun.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And the being sacrificed to Maomao’s curiosity probably wouldn&amp;#8217;t be able to move properly as a human being. They would be on a mattress, constantly cycling between injured and medicated, occasionally not able to sleep from overly strong medicine. They would lose the capacity to walk, and eating congee with a spoon would become impossible.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;If that was the case, surely they would only have to drink water from a soaked piece of cotton in the way she was doing now. That was trivial stuff. An existence that could bear and satisfy the curiosity she couldn’t restrain, how important would they be to her? She would probably end up harbouring emotions similar to adoration towards them.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She would wrap their body entirely in bandages, move their body so they didn’t get bedsores, and carefully wipe down their filthy body every night. She would wet their dry lips with a damp cloth, and feed them congee spoon by spoon. If they lose the energy to eat from a spoon, how about she feed them by mouth?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She would probably devote herself to them, as there would be no substitute for the most pitiful being.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Then, she might truly know the meaning of love.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(I’m thinking of bad things.)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao laughed, entertaining twisted desires with a sleeping person before her. If he could hear what was in her heart, she wouldn’t put it against him if he were to strike her down with a sword on the grounds of lese majeste.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was that moment.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi’s eyes cracked open.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Having accidentally made a noise, Maomao’s heart nearly jumped out of her chest.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi’s damaged fingers went straight for Maomao and grabbed onto her collar. Then she was pulled right over.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The next thing she knew, Maomao was hugging Jinshi with a single layer of bedding between them.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Silky hair touched Maomao’s cheeks; warm breathing tickled her neck.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao was looking at the white bedding. It wasn’t cheap stuff made from layers of straw, but high-class cotton padding.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Under this soft mattress, he was sure to have a blade for self-defence.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi could just wrestle her into a full nelson hold and she wouldn’t be able to stretch her arms out. As it turned out, as things were, he wasn’t going to hold her down to stab her deep in the head.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi was merely half-asleep. Her racing heart gradually slowed down.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao’s wide eyes regained their calmness, but her situation hadn’t changed. She wasn’t able to move with warm air breathing down her ear. It was the breathing of someone fast asleep, however.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao narrowed her eyes and snorted. The high-class fragrance was the smell of Jinshi’s incense, as well as another scent–what the madam had lit.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was an incense that gave people a good sleep and made them get closer. Maomao’s odd sentimental thinking might be thanks to that.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(Good-for-nothing hag as always.)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As her eyes closed, she thought she really should have just called for a courtesan just in case. She realised that she wasn’t able to slip away any more. At a time like this, it would be nice if Gaoshun intruded, and yet that hardworking man was quite possibly grinding tea for the madam.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;That being said, what a truly sinful man.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The fragrance in the air was pleasant, synergising with the incense that invited sleep–it took no time for Maomao to fall fast asleep as well.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;While worrying that he might slit her throat once she woke up, her consciousness winked out.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/ss-untitled/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-4607-6778a85c6b0bc' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20250104#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=4607&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-4607-6778a85c6b0bc' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-4607-6778a85c6b0bc' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/ss-untitled/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
