    <item>
      <title>11.10 The Night Visit</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/11-10-the-night-visit/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/11-10-the-night-visit/</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 24 Oct 2023 08:36:57 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;11.10 The Night&amp;nbsp;Visit&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/11-09-love/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The smell of the incense tickled Jinshi’s nose.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Don&amp;#8217;t you find the smell too intense?” he asked Suiren while he was having dinner.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Are you sure you&amp;#8217;re not just imagining things? You &lt;em&gt;have &lt;/em&gt;stayed in the western capital for a long time, so you have been limiting your use of incense,” his nanny said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You think so?”&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi picked up a piece of meat with his chopsticks. The dish was cooked with a generous amount of tender pork–fatty, yet seasoned to be light-tasting. Besides that, there was stir-fried eel, soft-shelled turtle broth, and so on and so forth–he felt that there were a lot of nutritionally enhancing dishes than usual.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Tonight’s dinner is entirely heavy,” he remarked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Are you sure you’re not just imagining things? You &lt;em&gt;have &lt;/em&gt;stayed in the western capital for a long time. Please eat it all.” Suiren chortled.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This is awfully suspicious&lt;/em&gt;, Jinshi thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He looked at the bodyguard in the room. “Wasn’t it Basen’s shift tonight?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Basen has a Ma family gathering, so he went home,” she replied.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The bath was even more suspicious.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What’s with the petals in the bath?” he asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Isn’t it a nice touch? You also have a medicated bath to improve circulation and metabolism,” she answered.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;With this much going on, even Jinshi could guess what was going on.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Back when Jinshi was at the inner palace, it was what the emperor came for. With Suiren manoeuvring about in the same manner in Jinshi’s palace, it could only mean that someone was going to come today.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Suiren, by any chance…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao will be coming today for the first time in a while. Haven’t you sent her a few letters?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi certainly did send her letters. They were simply catch-ups. He never ordered her to come to his palace. He only told her that he wanted to talk to her. He only politely wrote that she should get her work out of the way.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, wait a second. Isn’t it just Maomao who’s coming?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Your last meeting with her was when you alighted from the ship. Everyone has been busy since returning from the western capital. You have a correspondence saying that she could finally take a break.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“But like, this ambience doesn’t make sense. It’s just Maomao.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi looked over his bedroom. Off-season rose petals were scattered all over a brand new futon, which had been imbued with an incense that was more intense than usual. The canopy curtains were woven with see-through floral designs. Flower vases and beeswax candles have been placed all around the room, creating a romantic ambience with the wavering candlelight and sweet fragrance in the air.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He frantically extinguished the incense and candles, then opened up the windows to ventilate the room. He threw the petals scattered all over his bed into the bin and put away the vases.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Haaah, haaah.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“My, oh, my.”　&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s not &lt;em&gt;my oh my&lt;/em&gt;! What was up with this room?!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;This happened before when Maomao tried to treat Jinshi to the services at Rokushoukan. The process was very similar.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You have to set up a good vibe, right? Young master, it’s because your feelings with Maomao are mutual now,” Suiren said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“M-mutua…” Jinshi was flustered, so flustered he couldn’t look into the elderly woman’s eyes. He tried to feign calmness, but the corner of his lips rose.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It took far too long. Truly, your nanny was ever so worried. To think that, young master, who has been called the greatest treasure of our country, a relic of immortals who has descended upon the mortal world, a charmer of men and women of all ages, would be acting like a child his own age.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Um, no, that’s not—”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He wasn’t really hiding the matter about Maomao from Suiren, but he didn’t report it to her either. There were a lot of other people in the middle of a voyage, so they hardly had any time to themselves.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;So, he thought that no one would have noticed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Your nanny’s intuition as a woman is still on the mark.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi thought the elderly woman who was giggling, her eyes squinted in joy, was truly scary.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;With an uneasy expression, Jinshi scratched his head. “But like, it’s Maomao.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao herself is already over twenty years of age. She is knowledgeable even though she’s a virgin. I doubt she’d miss the implications of receiving a letter from a gentleman outside of work,” Suiren declared with a radiant smile.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, like I said, this room is–”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I thought it&amp;#8217;d be better if we were a little more direct.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s too direct! Any more and this—” Jinshi sat down on the edge of his bed and combed his fingers up his bangs. Gradually, his bashfulness burst into a different emotion. &lt;em&gt;No, I can’t, I can’t,&lt;/em&gt; Jinshi drank the water that had been left at his bedside.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Ah, that–”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Pleh!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There was a strange flavour in what was supposed to be water.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Hey, Suiren. What did you add in here?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It wasn’t poisonous, but it was related to what he just had for dinner.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“My, it was only a pinch, but you could tell? It’s not poison.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Of course I could tell. And &lt;em&gt;Maomao &lt;/em&gt;would be able to sniff it out.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Suiren unwillingly withdrew with the pitcher of water.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Haaaah.” Jinshi tried to restrain the thunderous beating of his heart with deep breaths.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;What was a man who was already of age, over twenty years old, getting all flustered for? All sorts of women have sneaked into his bedroom before.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-large"&gt;&lt;img width="396" height="576" src="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/capture-6.png" alt="" class="wp-image-4098" sizes="(max-width: 396px) 100vw, 396px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;All Jinshi knew about women was of him getting pinned down by a voluptuous body, moist bright red lips closing in. He even felt nauseous from their suffocatingly strong perfume. And then their shrill screams, as he watched them from the corner of his eyes as they got dragged away by a bodyguard by their hair.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;This was a frog in a well situation.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Frog…” Jinshi suddenly recalled an unpleasant word. He realised that the accidental glance at his crotch was a poisonous influence.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Settle down, settle down.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Should he chant sutras? Should he train?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;While such thoughts circled his mind, his guest arrived.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, yes, Maomao. It’s been a while. Please rise.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, Suiren-sama.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He heard a listless and unmotivated voice.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi adjusted his lapels, and headed for the living room as if nothing happened.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As always, Maomao had a slightly sleepy expression. She was carrying a large cloth bag in her arms.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s been a while,” he said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, Jinshi-sama,” she replied.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Anything you’d like to drink?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Going by routine, Suiren would be serving her tea. But it was different today. She filled a beautiful glass cup with distilled liquor of superior quality. The drink also had a high alcohol content–as much as Jinshi wanted to drink it, she wouldn’t let him as it would get in the way of work yesterday. She poured Maomao a generous serving of such.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Ohhhhh, oh, oh.” Maomao’s eyes shone, captivated by the aromatic amber liquid. He could see how badly she wanted to drink it with how much she was drooling over it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;But it also bothered Jinshi that she had completely forgotten about him. He made a showy display by setting some snacks before her. “It’s not good for you to only drink wine.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The walnuts, peanuts, and pine nuts were roasted and lightly salted. There were dried figs and longans as well, but Maomao was only enjoying the alcohol.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“How was work?” he asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The first day back, I autopsied a corpse that came from the weirdo tactician’s room.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It seems an outrageous thing happened right away.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Did the tactician do it?” Jinshi asked, just to confirm.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That old man didn’t have a hand in it. Physically. Also, it’s just the usual grudge from others.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She probably meant physically as in, Rakan had no physical strength. &lt;em&gt;Indeed&lt;/em&gt;, Jinshi recalled Rakan’s lack of stamina.&lt;em&gt; In spite of his ability to take action, he has no strength at all.&lt;/em&gt; So he thought, and he looked at Maomao. For her amazing pluck, she had no physical strength. She was unmotivated most of the time, and yet her ability to take action was no joke.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Like father, like daughter, indeed,&lt;/em&gt; Jinshi thought once again. At the same time, he was utterly terrified, wondering if Rakan knew that Maomao was currently in his palace.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao drank with pleasure. Suiren also set aside a share for Jinshi, but it had been diluted unlike Maomao’s. Jinshi himself preferred his alcohol to be on the stronger side, but he would lose to Maomao. If he were to drink the liquor straight, he would lose consciousness.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“How about Jinshi-sama?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No changes for me. I’ve finished my report to his imperial majesty, but my position hasn’t changed in particular. As always, absurd cases get delivered to my place. That being said, I’m not as busy as I was in the western capital.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Jinshi-sama is still young, so you have more than enough energy. Normally, you’d die from overwork.” Maomao drank the wine with great relish.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Have you had dinner yet?”&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, it is a pain to cook for one, so I have not.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I have leftovers from dinner, want some?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Suiren had enthusiastically made a lot. She must have cooked a portion for Maomao as well.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;‘As much as I would like to…” Maomao seemed hesitant. It was unusual since this girl in particular wasn’t one to hold back.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is there a reason why?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Let’s call it a reason.” Maomao cast down her eyes. “I also have made several preparations.”　&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi placed down the liquor.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao didn’t look any different from the usual, but he noticed that her skin was supple. The slight tan on her from the western capital has faded. She hadn’t drawn freckles. Instead, she had slapped on a very natural face powder.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The fragrance in the room had dissipated, but he could smell a hint of perfumed oil from her. Her hair was slightly damp, so she must have come over after taking a bath.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao drained the glass. “May I rinse my mouth?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yeah.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Normally, she would empty out the entire bottle and ask for more.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Jinshi-sama, shall we head in soon?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Y-yeah.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;What? Could I be dreaming?&lt;/em&gt; Jinshi thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Jinshi-sama, you&amp;#8217;re acting kind of clumsy?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Not at all.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao seemed as composed as she usually was, but she had a slightly bashful expression.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao, can I ask you this just in case?” Jinshi swallowed. &lt;em&gt;I &lt;/em&gt;have &lt;em&gt;to clarify this here&lt;/em&gt;, he thought. “You do understand what it means to enter my room, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s not to nurse me, nor to treat my injuries.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I have mentally readied myself and have made various preparations.” Maomao showed him what she brought in with her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi’s face reddened to unprecedented levels. He wanted to feign composure with all he could muster, but in the end, to appear calm, he turned away from Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Suiren had disappeared some time ago. The bodyguard who didn&amp;#8217;t, couldn’t, read the room was not around.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“How about a bath?” he asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I have taken one. I can go again if you desire so.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, it’s fine.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He knew that she had already taken a bath.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi placed a hand over his heart, trying to suppress the thunderous beating that could almost be heard.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Rather, it was Jinshi himself who wanted to wash up. He had already taken a bath, but he was sweaty, perhaps due to his drinking.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;However, it was a bit late to clean himself now, so he headed into the bedroom.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The choking smell of incense had been ventilated. The blatant petals on the bed and the strange medicated water were also gone.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Well then, speaking of what comes next.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He could no longer wait for the beating of his heart to settle. His face was flushed, but he didn’t need to care about it now.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi slowly lifted Maomao up into his arms. She had gained some weight, but she was still light. The scent of camellia oil emanated from her hair. “Can I?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I told you that I have done the preparations.” &lt;em&gt;Don’t make me repeat myself so many times&lt;/em&gt;, Maomao averted her eyes.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It wasn’t just Jinshi, Maomao was also nervous. Thinking that it wasn’t just him, Jinshi gained some composure.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What kind of preparations?” Jinshi asked Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I skipped breakfast and dinner.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;A surprising answer.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Why? Did you forget to eat from experimentation?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I skipped drinking water from half a day ago. I also thought about skipping the wine, but it was so delicious I helped myself to one glass.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Even water?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi couldn’t think of a reason why she needed to skip that.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If I were to have done this the proper way, I would have to skip meals three days prior, and water one day prior. My sincere apologies.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, what are you talking about?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s etiquette at Rokushoukan when a patron pays for a virgin, since you’re not allowed to soil yourself.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;No, I didn’t pay you or anything.” Jinshi’s face stiffened.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’m not certain if I could perform well.” Maomao had a serious look in her eyes. He had forgotten that she had the soul of an artisan that would give her all into anything she did.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi, taken aback, let out a breath. She wasn’t going to evade and run away like she did before. He was very happy that she was responding positively to this.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Also, can I have some water?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Are you thirsty?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No.” Maomao opened her large cloth bag. Inside was a pack of medicine. There was also a jumble of things he was not used to seeing.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What’s this?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“A blend of ground cherry root, four o’clock flower and balsam seeds.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;These were all plants that sounded familiar, but he also remembered this very combination.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Aren’t these all plants you told me to keep an eye out for at the inner palace?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That’s right.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The inner palace was where the emperor’s children were born and raised. Factors that could impede it have to be eliminated.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Why did you bring such things?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“For you to double-check the contents. It is not for Jinshi-sama, rest assured. I will be the one&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;taking it.” Maomao was serious. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She continued, “I also have a tool that can physically block it, but its effectiveness is low. It would be better for Jinshi-sama to not wear it if you don’t like it.” She took out a tubular item that had been carefully wrapped up. “It’s made from cow intestines. There’s no problem with whether it’ll fit Jinshi-sama…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She surreptitiously packed away the thing that was made from cow intestines.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“So, these are contraceptives?” he asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“And you saying that it took you a while to prepare all these would mean…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’ve only gathered what I could get my hands on at the pleasure district.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Blood suddenly drained from Jinshi’s face. His entire body grew cold.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Since I have accepted Jinshi-sama’s feelings, I agree to be in a relationship with you. But I need to clarify where I stand in this. I have no intention of becoming Empress Gyokuyou’s enemy.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi bit his lips.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He forgot himself. He lost sight of his own identity, hadn’t he?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;While Maomao may know him as Jinshi, what about the people around him? What do they call him?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The Moon Prince–Ka Zuigetsu, the emperor’s younger brother.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The crown prince Empress Gyokuyou bore was still young. And in the imperial court, there were still people supporting Jinshi as the crown prince.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Therefore, what would happen were he to sire a child with a girl he had even yet to handfast?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Moreover, if people were to know that his partner was Maomao, Kan Rakan’s daughter?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;They would not be able to continue with their secretive ambiguous relationship as things stood.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I have also tracked my menstrual cycle. Tonight is a relatively safe day. Again, worry not if it fails. I know ways to deal with it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao probably wasn’t lying. She would definitely deal with it if she did conceive. There was no way she would raise the child in secret.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As cold as it was, considering how it could become a trigger, it was the right call.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi hugged Maomao tightly.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It wasn’t the lust built up from just now. He was racked with remorse; he almost grounded his teeth.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Sorry, I made you worry.” Jinshi rested his forehead on Maomao’s shoulder. She patted his back.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s all right.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi reluctantly let go of Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Suppressing his feelings of disappointment, he laid down on his bed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Jinshi-sama.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You should head back today. If you like, take dinner back with you. The food’s cold by now, but still, you must be hungry.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“But–”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s fine. Just go. Drink water. We can’t have you fainting.” Jinshi covered his face with both hands.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Understood.” Maomao packed up her bag and left the room. “In that case, excuse me…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;As she went out, she muttered something.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“This is fine. That’s all for today.” Jinshi had to clarify his position. He cannot keep his position as the imperial brother forever. He had to indicate to Empress Gyokuyou and Consort Rifa that he wasn’t their enemy.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He had no other option than to abdicate the position of the emperor’s younger brother, and step down from being an imperial.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What do I do?” Jinshi was tormented.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Thus he failed to hear what Maomao mumbled the moment she left.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;I also thought we could do it without going all the way.&amp;#8221;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He was just that preoccupied with his own thoughts.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;T/N: 壬氏さま、なんかぎくしゃくしてません？&lt;br&gt;First pass translation: &amp;#8220;Jinshi-sama, you&amp;#8217;re kinda stiff?&amp;#8221;&lt;br&gt;Me: &amp;#8230;Maybe not the best translation for that line, no. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/11-11-aduos-truth/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/11-10-the-night-visit/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-4086-677889712526a' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20250104#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=4086&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-4086-677889712526a' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-4086-677889712526a' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/11-10-the-night-visit/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
