    <item>
      <title>14.13 Tomato</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-13-tomato/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-13-tomato/</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 11 Dec 2024 08:21:38 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;14.13 Tomato&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-12-spell/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;At Rakan’s residence, the sounds of soil being tilled filled the air.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The sight caught me by surprise in the beginning, but I’m used to it now&lt;/em&gt;, Junjie thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Rahan’s older brother was ploughing the fields. He ploughed the fields all throughout his time at the western capital, and he was doing so even at the imperial capital. Moreover, it was in a garden within an estate in a prime location, right in the heart of the imperial capital.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Junjie had his reservations about ploughing at Gyoku’en’s residence in the western capital. However, the landscaping of the garden was irrelevant during times of emergency food shortage due to the locust plague.&amp;nbsp; &lt;em&gt;The figure of the man single-mindedly producing crops for the people had been magnificent, &lt;/em&gt;he thought, but…&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Isn’t he overdoing it?&lt;/em&gt; he started to think.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Junjie was told that Rahan’s older brother’s name wasn’t Rahan. The man was the older brother of Rahan, whom was apparently the son of the master of this estate. &lt;em&gt;Then would that make Rahan’s older brother be his son too?&lt;/em&gt; he had asked, but when told that he was wrong, Junjie, a commoner, could only tilt his head in confusion at the complicated familial relation.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Speaking of complicated, the relation of the people in this residence was also complicated.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Heeey, Junjie.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Sifan called out to him in a friendly tone. The child was an orphan picked up by the master of the estate, relatively close in age to Junjie. She was actually a few years younger, but he didn’t feel much of an age gap since she was clever. Wufan and Liufan were by her side as always. Their strange names were to make it easier for the master who picked them up, but Junjie thought it made them sound like criminals.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;But surprisingly, the people in question seem to like it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The three of them were carrying cleaning equipment like brooms and buckets.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What is it?” Junjie asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Looks like we’ll be getting another freeloader. We’ve been told to prepare the room for them to stay at. Give us a hand,” Sifan said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Junjie didn’t get idle since Sifan always gave him work to do.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Got it. Did Rakan-sama bring someone in?” he asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Nah, it’s Rahan-sama this time. The Moon Prince requested him to look after a sick person,” she said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Oh?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Junjie followed after Sifan and the others. Rakan’s residence had a lot of unused rooms for its size. The estate was built to be large because it had been around since the relocation of the capital, but there were too many empty rooms since there were few Ra blood relatives and barely any servants too.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Sifan headed for one of the outbuildings. “This’ the place.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There was another outbuilding nearby.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Isn’t it close to Yao-sama and En’en-sama’s room?” Junjie asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That’s right.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s a sick person, but would it be okay to have them so close to a guest’s room?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yao-sama and En’en-sama are court physician assistants, right? In times like this we’ll have them work for us. I mean, they &lt;em&gt;are &lt;/em&gt;paying us, but I kinda don’t understand why they’re here.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I think so too.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Anyway, an underling has one thing to do. And that is to complete what we are told to do in no time.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Under Sifan’s guidance, they started to clean the outbuilding. The building may be small, but it had a toilet at close proximity and had good sunlight too.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Sifan, the wall has a hole.” Wufan pointed at the hole.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then we’ll check for all the spots that need repairs. We’ll report to Sanfan-neesan later and get them fixed,” Sifan said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Got it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8211;&lt;em&gt;It&lt;/em&gt;,” Liufan echoed Wufan.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Would it get cold if we plug up the hole as well?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If they’re a sick person, it might be better if we prepare them something like a brazier instead,” Junjie said as he swept the floor. There were spots here and there that bothered him, but the interior was surprisingly clean.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yeah, floor heating would have been nice, but they don’t have it here in the imperial capital.” Sifan said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Floor heating?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Rich families in the north have it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The floor gets &lt;em&gt;really &lt;/em&gt;warm,” Wufan said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8211;&lt;em&gt;Warm&lt;/em&gt;,” Liufan echoed again.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Liufan’s language skills were poor for his age. According to what Junjie heard, Wufan and Liufan were picked up by Rakan after Sifan was, so if Sifan hadn’t been around, these two might have already died by the roadside, Junjie thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Junjie opened the window. When he did so, he saw bright red things fill his vision.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Woah!” Junjie yelled out in shock. For a moment he thought the garish red colours were lumps of meat or blood, but upon closer look they were fruits.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Ahh, those,” Sifan said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What Rahan’s older brother dried.” Wufan said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8211;&lt;em&gt;Dried&lt;/em&gt;.” said Liufan.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Junjie knew them too. There had been strange red fruit seedlings being planted and grown during summer. &lt;em&gt;Although Rahan’s older brother had called them a vegetable, they remind me of jujubes,&lt;/em&gt; Junjie thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Rahan’s older brother’s father had apparently ordered them for ornamental purposes, but since they were edible,&amp;nbsp; they were cultivating them as food. It had a high water content, was sour and could be eaten raw, boiled or grilled. Rahan’s older brother later continued the research, and it seems he was now testing to see if it could be processed into a dried food.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Junjie thought that a farmer acknowledged by even the Moon Prince does things differently indeed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Heeey.” Right on cue, Rahan’s older bother came up with a hoe in hand. “Sorry, it’s still in the process of drying. Will you be using this outbuilding?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Rahan’s older brother was dripping with sweat. He had just finished with his work. It was already the season for frost, and yet he was lightly dressed, his skin flushed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When they were at the western capital, he clearly worked in only his underwear, but he hadn’t sported that look since coming to the imperial capital. His reasoning was that he couldn’t dress like that before young ladies.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Are Maomao and Chue not considered young ladies?&lt;/em&gt; Junjie thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Are they drying well? Not much longer perhaps. I’ll pack it away for now.” Rahan’s older brother picked up the red fruits one by one to check if they had dried.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’ll help you,” Junjie said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Okay. If I can’t use this building, then we’ll carry it to the storehouse over there.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It looks like they were cleaning the outbuilding because Rahan’s older brother had been using it as a storehouse. He had also used it to store farming tools, so they will need to make a few round trips.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is there yet another guest coming?” Rahan’s older brother asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. A sick person will be joining us. The Moon Prince’s orders,” Junjie said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“A sick person, huh? Then, I’ll have to feed them a lot of vegetables. Do you know what kind of illness they have?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I didn’t hear that far.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When they came back after carrying all the red fruits to the storehouse, Yao and En’en have returned.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Rahan’s older brother immediately tidied up his appearance and smoothed over his expression. He was good looking, but his actions looked vaguely ridiculous. “En’en-saaan!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The two of them have returned to the outbuilding. Yao and En’en’s working hours didn’t coincide often, so En’en generally waited for Yao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Ju– Rahan’s older brother.” En’en looked at Junjie, then corrected herself.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Are you done with work? If you are tired, how about I prepare you vegetables that would help you recover from exhaustion and make your skin beautiful?” Rahan’s older brother leaned against the detached building’s pillar with a smile.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Thank you very much. It would be great if you could leave it by the kitchen like always.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Understood!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Junjie has witnessed this exchange many times. And he decided against mentioning that it was more a conversation between a cook and a supplier. Everyone wanted to say it. Even Sifan, Wufan, and Liufan were on the verge of making quips–it wasn’t what Junjie as the newcomer could bring up.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is there anything bothering you?” Rahan’s older brother then asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Let’s see. It’s gotten cold, so I would love to have spices that could warm the body, if you have any of the sort,” En’en said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Understood. Maomao had requested me for ginger so I’ll bring that over too. Also, there is an interesting ingredient that I’ve grown–I’ll bring that too.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He was taking orders, full stop. &lt;em&gt;We have to switch to daily conversations now&lt;/em&gt;, Junjie thought, but Rahan’s older brother was only recommending vegetables.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Hello, Rahan’s older brother. Thank you for your vegetables as always,” Yao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No worries. I&amp;#8217;m just doing what I enjoy.” Rahan’s older brother responded naturally to Yao’s thanks.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;En’en was staring at Rahan’s older brother intently, looking like she was making sure of something.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“By the way, have you heard that a sick person will be coming to this outbuilding?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, we have a letter from Maomao with various instructions. Most importantly, it seems she is malnourished, so we’ll be having her eat a lot of Rahan’s older brother’s produce,” Yao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Was it his imagination that the way Yao spoke to Rahan&amp;#8217;s older brother was more proper than En&amp;#8217;en?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;At least, she was speaking to him as a neighbour, not a supplier.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The letter says the patient is still a fourteen year old girl, so we’ll have to look after her properly,” En’en said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“A &lt;em&gt;fourteen &lt;/em&gt;year old girl… We must keep her far away from that Rahan rascal at all costs!” Rahan’s older brother’s gaze grew sharp.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That’s right. We must keep Rahan-sama far away from here at all costs.”&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It looked like En’en had made a different resolution.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“En’en, I don’t think we can say anything since we’re freeloaders. But if we have a sick person coming, he’d rely on us, wouldn’t he?” Yao said bashfully.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Junjie, having stayed at Rakan’s residence for half a year, had his thoughts.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The woman called Yao may look mature, but she was mentally immature. This could be attributed to her good upbringing, but En’en, her follower, was to blame in further restricting her knowledge of the outside world.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;This was why she worries over her own actions while acting recklessly. Speaking of how Junjie could assess Yao with this much detail, it was Sifan. Sifan was more mature than her actual age, so she was good at reading the subtleties of other people’s hearts. &lt;em&gt;She’s quite capable as a servant&lt;/em&gt;, he thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The conversations related to Yao couldn’t be said in the presence of the other adults, Sanfan especially, and Wufan and Liufan were much too young. As a result, she would talk to Junjie often. As a result, he became knowledgeable of the personal relationships within the estate.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yao-san. It’s a great help that you are thinking of how you can be useful to others, but if Rahan is forcing you to do so, let me know. That curly-haired cold-blooded glasses is my younger brother after all. I’ll tell him off for you.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, he’s not forcing me.”　&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then you can be more at ease. Otherwise, you’ll end up tiring yourself out because of the patient that will be coming now. If it’s out of a sense of obligation, we can arrange for other doctors, can’t we? Since it’s the Moon Prince’s request, they’ll be paying us as much as we want. What’s more, we can call for Maomao. Granduncle Luomen comes back every so often too. You can relax,” Rahan’s older brother said and slapped Yao’s shoulder.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yao, although surprised, didn’t seem discomforted by Rahan’s older brother and smiled lightly.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;En’en watched them with a sullen look. Apparently it was within permissible range.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Sifan came up beside Junjie. “Not going as planned, is it?” she muttered.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What is not going as planned?” Junjie asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Nah, the direction of the arrow has only shifted a little. It seems to be progressing really smoothly. It would be easier to have Sanfan-neesan dealt with too, however.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is that so?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As Sifan shook her head as if to say, “Not going as planned,” she dumped out the filthy washing water from the bucket.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-14-starvation/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-13-tomato/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-5155-67788971b35fc' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20250104#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=5155&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-5155-67788971b35fc' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-5155-67788971b35fc' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-13-tomato/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
